Handson5 - Angular Reactive Forms
Task 1: Build a Reactive Form with FormBuilder

Goal: Create a Reactive Form using FormBuilder.

1. Generate Component

ng g c pages/reactive-enrollment-form

Add Route

path:'enroll-reactive'

2. Import ReactiveFormsModule.

3. Build Form

constructor(private fb:FormBuilder){}

ngOnInit(){
 this.enrollForm=this.fb.group({
 studentName:['',[Validators.required,Validators.minLength(3)]],
 studentEmail:['',[Validators.required,Validators.email]],
 courseId:[null,Validators.required],
 preferredSemester:['Odd',Validators.required],
 agreeToTerms:[false,Validators.requiredTrue]
 });
}

4. HTML

<form [formGroup]="enrollForm">

<input formControlName="studentName">

<input formControlName="studentEmail">

<input formControlName="courseId">

<select formControlName="preferredSemester">
<option>Odd</option>
<option>Even</option>
</select>

<input type="checkbox"
formControlName="agreeToTerms">

<button
[disabled]="enrollForm.invalid">
Submit
</button>

</form>

5. Submit

onSubmit(){
 console.log(this.enrollForm.value);
 console.log(this.enrollForm.getRawValue());
}

Difference

value -> excludes disabled controls

getRawValue() -> includes disabled controls

Expected:
Reactive form works successfully.

Task 2: Custom Validators & FormArray

Custom Validator

noCourseCode(control:AbstractControl){
 return control.value?.startsWith('XX')
 ? {noCourseCode:true}
 : null;
}

Display Error

<span *ngIf="enrollForm.get('courseId')?.errors?.['noCourseCode']">
Course code starting with XX is not allowed.
</span>

Async Validator

simulateEmailCheck(control:AbstractControl){
 return new Promise(resolve=>{
  setTimeout(()=>{
   if(control.value=='test@example.com')
      resolve({emailTaken:true});
   else
      resolve(null);
  },800);
 });
}

Apply

studentEmail:['',
[Validators.required,Validators.email],
[this.simulateEmailCheck]]

FormArray

additionalCourses=this.fb.array([]);

addCourse(){
 this.additionalCourses.push(
   this.fb.control('')
 );
}

removeCourse(i:number){
 this.additionalCourses.removeAt(i);
}

Getter

get additionalCoursesList(){
 return this.enrollForm.get('additionalCourses') as FormArray;
}

Expected Output

• XX101 shows validation error.
• test@example.com shows Email Taken after 800ms.
• Additional courses can be added and removed dynamically.

